      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TYCOON HARRY (1) ticks plenty of boxes on his recent form, winning by 0.5L as the race favourite most recently in this grade. This looks to shape similarly for Nottle from a good draw and while he does rise in weight, it's hard to see anything turning the tables on him today. KAY TEE WHY (2) had been racing in stronger company prior to the break, flying home from the back over 1200m most recently. Back to 1000m off a freshen today and he comes into this without a trial. Has a fantastic record at this track and trip and first-up, and he can land the knockout blow. SIXINCH HEELS (8) will be fitter for a recent trial coming into this and she's a first-up winner in the past. Fiore rides her as she remains down in the weights and a forward showing is expected first-up. CASTLE ROAD (4) can bounce back to form dropping down to 1000m again today and with the aid of an inside draw. PINGERS (6) is better than she showed last time out and can bounce back.",
